2103.definition: [Εὔβουλος] from {{G2095}} and {{G1014}}; good-willer; Eubulus, a Christian

2104.definition: [εὐγενής] from {{G2095}} and {{G1096}}; well born, i.e. (literally) high in rank, or (figuratively) generous

2105.definition: [εὐδία] feminine from {{G2095}} and the alternate of {{G2203}} (as the god of the weather); a clear sky, i.e. fine weather

2106.definition: [εὐδοκέω] from {{G2095}} and {{G1380}}; to think well of, i.e. approve (an act); specially, to approbate (a person or thing)

2107.definition: [εὐδοκία] from a presumed compound of {{G2095}} and the base of {{G1380}}; satisfaction, i.e. (subjectively) delight, or (objectively) kindness, wish, purpose

2110.definition: [εὐεργέτης] from {{G2095}} and the base of {{G2041}}; a worker of good, i.e. (specially) a philanthropist

2111.definition: [εὔθετος] from {{G2095}} and a derivative of {{G5087}}; well placed, i.e. (figuratively) appropriate

2112.definition: [εὐθέως] adverb from {{G2117}}; directly, i.e. at once or soon

2113.definition: [εὐθυδρομέω] from {{G2117}} and {{G1408}}; to lay a straight course, i.e. sail direct

2114.definition: [εὐθυμέω] from {{G2115}}; to cheer up, i.e. (intransitively) be cheerful; neuter comparative (adverbially) more cheerfully

2115.definition: [εὔθυμος] from {{G2095}} and {{G2372}}; in fine spirits, i.e. cheerful

2116.definition: [εὐθύνω] from {{G2117}}; to straighten (level); technically, to steer

2117.definition: [εὐθύς] perhaps from {{G2095}} and {{G5087}}; straight, i.e. (literally) level, or (figuratively) true; adverbially (of time) at once

2119.definition: [εὐκαιρέω] from {{G2121}}; to have good time, i.e. opportunity or leisure

2123.definition: [εὐκοπώτερος] comparative of a compound of {{G2095}} and {{G2873}}; better for toil, i.e. more facile

2124.definition: [εὐλάβεια] from {{G2126}}; properly, caution, i.e. (religiously) reverence (piety); by implication, dread (concretely)

2125.definition: [εὐλαβέομαι] middle voice from {{G2126}}; to be circumspect, i.e. (by implication) to be apprehensive; religiously, to reverence

2126.definition: [εὐλαβής] from {{G2095}} and {{G2983}}; taking well (carefully), i.e. circumspect (religiously, pious)

2127.definition: [εὐλογέω] from a compound of {{G2095}} and {{G3056}}; to speak well of, i.e. (religiously) to bless (thank or invoke a benediction upon, prosper)

2129.definition: [εὐλογία] from the same as {{G2127}}; fine speaking, i.e. elegance of language; commendation ("eulogy"), i.e. (reverentially) adoration; religiously, benediction; by implication, consecration; by extension, benefit or largess

2130.definition: [εὐμετάδοτος] from {{G2095}} and a presumed derivative of {{G3330}}; good at imparting, i.e. liberal

2132.definition: [εὐνοέω] from a compound of {{G2095}} and {{G3563}}; to be well- minded, i.e. reconcile

2133.definition: [εὔνοια] from the same as {{G2132}}; kindness; euphemistically, conjugal duty

2135.definition: [εὐνοῦχος] from εὐνή (a bed) and {{G2192}}; a castrated person (such being employed in Oriental bed-chambers); by extension an impotent or unmarried man; by implication, a chamberlain (state-officer)

2136.definition: [Εὐοδία] from the same as {{G2137}}; fine travelling; Euodia, a Christian woman

2137.definition: [εὐοδόω] from a compound of {{G2095}} and {{G3598}}; to help on the road, i.e. (passively) succeed in reaching; figuratively, to succeed in business affairs

2138.definition: [εὐπειθής] from {{G2095}} and {{G3982}}; good for persuasion, i.e. (intransitively) complaint

2139.definition: [εὐπερίστατος] from {{G2095}} and a derivative of a presumed compound of {{G4012}} and {{G2476}}; well standing around, i.e. (a competitor) thwarting (a racer) in every direction (figuratively, of sin in genitive case)

2140.definition: [εὐποιΐα] from a compound of {{G2095}} and {{G4160}}; well-doing, i.e. beneficence

2141.definition: [εὐπορέω] from a compound of {{G2090}} and the base of {{G4197}}; (intransitively) to be good for passing through, i.e. (figuratively) have pecuniary means

2142.definition: [εὐπορία] from the same as {{G2141}}; pecuniary resources

2143.definition: [εὐπρέπεια] from a compound of {{G2095}} and {{G4241}}; good suitableness, i.e. gracefulness

2144.definition: [εὐπρόσδεκτος] from {{G2095}} and a derivative of {{G4327}}; well-received, i.e. approved, favorable

2145.definition: [εὐπρόσεδρος] from {{G2095}} and the same as {{G4332}}; sitting well towards, i.e. (figuratively) assiduous (neuter, diligent service)

2146.definition: [εὐπροσωπέω] from a compound of {{G2095}} and {{G4383}}; to be of good countenance, i.e. (figuratively) to make a display

2147.definition: [εὑρίσκω] , a prolonged form of a primary             εὕρω,      which                                 (together with another cognate form)             εὑρέω    is used for it in all the tenses                                except the present and imperfect; to find (literally or figuratively)

2148.definition: [Εὐροκλύδων] from Εὖρος (the east wind) and {{G2830}}; a storm from the East (or southeast), i.e. (in modern phrase) a Levanter

2150.definition: [εὐσέβεια] from {{G2152}}; piety; specially, the gospel scheme

2151.definition: [εὐσεβέω] from {{G2152}}; to be pious, i.e. (towards God) to worship, or (towards parents) to respect (support)

2154.definition: [εὔσημος] from {{G2095}} and the base of {{G4591}}; well indicated, i.e. (figuratively) significant

2155.definition: [εὔσπλαγχνος] from {{G2095}} and {{G4698}}; well compassioned, i.e. sympathetic

2158.definition: [εὐσχήμων] from {{G2095}} and {{G4976}}; well-formed, i.e. (figuratively) decorous, noble (in rank)

2159.definition: [εὐτόνως] adverb from a compound of {{G2095}} and a derivative of τείνω (to stretch); in a well-strung manner, i.e. (figuratively) intensely (in a good sense, cogently; in a bad one, fiercely)

2160.definition: [εὐτραπελία] from a compound of {{G2095}} and a derivative of the base of {{G5157}} (meaning well-turned, i.e. ready at repartee, jocose); witticism, i.e. (in a vulgar sense) ribaldry

2161.definition: [Εὔτυχος] from {{G2095}} and a derivative of {{G5177}}; well- fated, i.e. fortunate; Eutychus, a young man

2163.definition: [εὔφημος] from {{G2095}} and {{G5345}}; well spoken of, i.e. reputable

2164.definition: [εὐφορέω] from {{G2095}} and {{G5409}}; to bear well, i.e. be fertile

2165.definition: [εὐφραίνω] from {{G2095}} and {{G5424}}; to put (middle voice or passively, be) in a good frame of mind, i.e. rejoice

2166.definition: [Εὐφράτης] of foreign origin (compare {{H6578}}); Euphrates, a river of Asia

2168.definition: [εὐχαριστέω] from {{G2170}}; to be grateful, i.e. (actively) to express gratitude (towards); specially, to say grace at a meal

2169.definition: [εὐχαριστία] from {{G2170}}; gratitude; actively, grateful language (to God, as an act of worship)

2170.definition: [εὐχάριστος] from {{G2095}} and a derivative of {{G5483}}; well favored, i.e. (by implication) grateful

2171.definition: [εὐχή] from {{G2172}}; properly, a wish, expressed as a petition to God, or in votive obligation

2172.definition: [εὔχομαι] middle voice of a primary verb; to wish; by implication, to pray to God

2173.definition: [εὔχρηστος] from {{G2095}} and {{G5543}}; easily used, i.e. useful

2174.definition: [εὐψυχέω] from a compound of {{G2095}} and {{G5590}}; to be in good spirits, i.e. feel encouraged

2175.definition: [εὐωδία] from a compound of {{G2095}} and a derivative of {{G3605}}; good-scentedness, i.e. fragrance

2176.definition: [εὐώνυμος] from {{G2095}} and {{G3686}}; properly, well-named (good-omened), i.e. the left (which was the lucky side among the pagan Greeks); neuter as adverbial, at the left hand

2179.definition: [Ἐφεσῖνος] from {{G2181}}; Ephesine, or situated at Ephesus

2180.definition: [Ἐφέσιος] from {{G2181}}; an Ephesian or inhabitant of Ephesus

2181.definition: [Ἔφεσος] probably of foreign origin; Ephesus, a city of Asia Minor

2182.definition: [ἐφευρετής] from a compound of {{G1909}} and {{G2147}}; a discoverer, i.e. contriver

2183.definition: [ἐφημερία] from {{G2184}}; diurnality, i.e. (specially) the quotidian rotation or class of the Jewish priests' service at the Temple, as distributed by families

2184.definition: [ἐφήμερος] from {{G1909}} and {{G2250}}; for a day ("ephemeral"), i.e. diurnal

2185.definition: [ἐφικνέομαι] from {{G1909}} and a cognate of {{G2240}}; to arrive upon, i.e. extend to

2186.definition: [ἐφίστημι] from {{G1909}} and {{G2476}}; to stand upon, i.e. be present (in various applications, friendly or otherwise, usually literal);

2187.definition: [Ἐφραίμ] of Hebrew origin ({{H669}} or better {{H6085}}); Ephraim, a place in Palestine

2189.definition: [ἔχθρα] feminine of {{G2190}}; hostility; by implication, a reason for opposition

2190.definition: [ἐχθρός] from a primary ἔχθω (to hate); hateful (passively, odious, or actively, hostile); usually as a noun, an adversary (especially Satan)

2191.definition: [ἔχιδνα] of uncertain origin; an adder or other poisonous snake (literally or figuratively)

2192.definition: [ἔχω] ,    including an alternate form      σχέω;  (used in certain tenses only) a primary verb; to hold (used in very various applications, literally or figuratively, direct or remote; such as possession; ability, contiuity, relation, or condition)

2193.definition: [ἕως] of uncertain affinity; a conjunction, preposition and adverb of continuance, until (of time and place)

2194.definition: [Ζαβουλών] of Hebrew origin ({{H2074}}); Zabulon (i.e. Zebulon), a region of Palestine

2195.definition: [Ζακχαῖος] of Hebrew origin (compare {{H2140}}); Zacchæus, an Israelite

2196.definition: [Ζαρά] of Hebrew origin ({{H2226}}); Zara, (i.e. Zerach), an Israelite

2197.definition: [Ζαχαρίας] of Hebrew origin ({{H2148}}); Zacharias (i.e. Zechariah), the name of two Israelites

2198.definition: [ζάω] a primary verb; to live (literally or figuratively)

2199.definition: [Ζεβεδαῖος] of Hebrew origin (compare {{H2067}}); Zebedæus, an Israelite

2200.definition: [ζεστός] from {{G2204}}; boiled, i.e. (by implication) calid (figuratively, fervent)
